   <TEXT>
   <S PAR='1' RSNT='1' SNO='1'>A CONTRITE, RIGHT, WILLING, AND BROKEN SPIRIT</S>
   <S PAR='2' RSNT='1' SNO='2'>In Psalms 34:18 you have a "contrite spirit," and in Psalms 51:10, a "right spirit."</S>
   <S PAR='3' RSNT='1' SNO='3'>In Psalms 51:12 is a "willing spirit."</S>
   <S PAR='4' RSNT='1' SNO='4'>Psalms 51 is a prayer of David.</S>
   <S PAR='5' RSNT='1' SNO='5'>In verse 10 he says, "Renew a right spirit within me."</S>
   <S PAR='6' RSNT='1' SNO='6'>Then in verse 12 he says, "Restore unto me the joy of thy salvation and sustain me with a willing spirit" lit.</S>
   <S PAR='7' RSNT='1' SNO='7'>. Then in verse 17 is a "broken spirit."</S>
   <S PAR='8' RSNT='1' SNO='8'>Psalms 51 shows us a contrite spirit, a right spirit, a willing spirit, and a broken spirit.</S>
   <S PAR='9' RSNT='1' SNO='9'>MY SPIRIT</S>
   <S PAR='10' RSNT='1' SNO='10'>Psalms 77:3 says, "I complained, and my spirit was overwhelmed."</S>
   <S PAR='11' RSNT='1' SNO='11'>Psalms 77:6 says, "I call to remembrance my song in the night: I commune with mine own heart: and my spirit made diligent search."</S>
   <S PAR='12' RSNT='1' SNO='12'>I communed to myself with my heart, but my spirit made a diligent search in the presence of God.</S>
   <S PAR='13' RSNT='1' SNO='13'>A STEADFAST SPIRIT</S>
   <S PAR='14' RSNT='1' SNO='14'>Psalms 78:8 says that the children of Israel were not steadfast in their spirit with God.</S>
   <S PAR='15' RSNT='1' SNO='15'>We need a steadfast spirit with God.</S>
   <S PAR='16' RSNT='1' SNO='16'>We don't only need to make up our mind or have a strong will, but we need to have a steadfast spirit with God.</S>
   <S PAR='17' RSNT='1' SNO='17'>GOD WEIGHS OUR SPIRIT</S>
   <S PAR='18' RSNT='1' SNO='18'>Proverbs 16:2 says, "All the ways of a man are clean in his own eyes; but the Lord weigheth the spirits."</S>
   <S PAR='19' RSNT='1' SNO='19'>God puts your spirit on the balance, on the scale, to weigh it.</S>
   <S PAR='20' RSNT='1' SNO='20'>God cares for what we are in our spirit.</S>
   <S PAR='21' RSNT='1' SNO='21'>We consider our ways; He weighs our spirits.</S>
   <S PAR='22' RSNT='1' SNO='22'>A SEEKING SPIRIT</S>
   <S PAR='23' RSNT='1' SNO='23'>Isaiah 26:9 says, "With my soul have I desired Thee in the night; yea, with my spirit within me will I seek Thee early."</S>
   <S PAR='24' RSNT='1' SNO='24'>To desire the Lord is something of the soul, but to seek the Lord is something of the spirit.</S>
   <S PAR='25' RSNT='1' SNO='25'>With my soul I desired thee.</S>
   <S PAR='26' RSNT='1' SNO='26'>With the spirit within me I seek thee.</S>
   <S PAR='27' RSNT='1' SNO='27'>We have to seek the Lord with our spirit.</S>
   <S PAR='28' RSNT='1' SNO='28'>A CONTRITE AND HUMBLE SPIRIT</S>
   <S PAR='29' RSNT='1' SNO='29'>In Isaiah 57:15-16 you have a contrite and humble spirit.</S>
   <S PAR='30' RSNT='1' SNO='30'>Verse 16 says that the Lord would not be so hard with us.</S>
   <S PAR='31' RSNT='1' SNO='31'>If He would be too hard with us, then our spirit would fail.</S>
   <S PAR='32' RSNT='1' SNO='32'>Sometimes the Lord allows certain things to happen to us, but still there is a certain kind of limitation because the Lord is careful about our spirit.</S>
   <S PAR='33' RSNT='1' SNO='33'>He knows our spirit cannot suffer that much in a certain hard situation, so He would not allow too much suffering in order that our spirit would not fail.</S>
   <S PAR='34' RSNT='1' SNO='34'>This tells us that God is concerned for our spirit.</S>
   <S PAR='35' RSNT='1' SNO='35'>A PROVOKED SPIRIT</S>
   <S PAR='36' RSNT='1' SNO='36'>Psalms 106:33 tells us that the children of Israel provoked Moses' spirit.</S>
   <S PAR='37' RSNT='1' SNO='37'>This shows us that the spirit is the deepest part of a person and the most important part.</S>
   <S PAR='38' RSNT='1' SNO='38'>I may provoke your mind.</S>
   <S PAR='39' RSNT='1' SNO='39'>That doesn't mean much.</S>
   <S PAR='40' RSNT='1' SNO='40'>But if I provoke your spirit, that is really something serious.</S>
   </TEXT>
